title: Relative to a given criterion of validity, an axiomatic system is sound if every theorem is valid, and it is complete (or, more specifically, weakly complete) if every valid WFF is a theorem. The axiomatic system PM can be shown to be both sound and complete relative to the criterion of validity already given (see above Validity in PC).
pid: 3b44e440-fd9d-4a64-9dbe-0501b99d6d3a
